		<content_encoded><![CDATA[<a href="http://www.crimethinc.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2007/09/under_big.jpg" title="When this is the only cover image you can find anywhere, you know it's going to be a hard book to track down." rel="lightbox" class="smallitem"><img src="http://www.crimethinc.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2007/09/under_small.jpg" alt="under_small.jpg" /></a>Distraught CrimethInc. workers are desperately seeking a copy of <a href="http://www.amazon.com/Under-Lens-People-Account-Resistance/dp/0973357517" target="_blank"><em>Under The Lens Of The People: Our Account Of The Peoples' Resistance To The FTAA, Quebec City, April 2001</em></a>, which we need to proceed with our current epic publishing project. If anyone has a copy of this book or knows where one can be found, please get in touch with us (<a href="mailto:pfm@crimethinc.com">pfm@crimethinc.com</a>) immediately. Borrowing it—or perhaps even receiving top-quality scans of pages over the internet—would probably suffice. We really count on the international network for help with challenges like this. Thanks so much in advance! [Yes, we know Amazon and AK Press both list it as available—it's not.] ]]></content_encoded>
